The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, June 14, 2004  Calcutta Column

	Work on the flyover on JL Nehru Road has been stalled, but huge blocks of cement, bricks and iron rods have been piled up in the middle of the road, from Lindsay Street to the Jeevan Deep crossing. Earlier, the civic officials were busy with the election. Its time they took the initiative to repair the road. 
	Sumant Poddar, Kyd Street. 
	The railways should reserve a compartment on all local trains for the aged, physically challenged and ailing passengers. It would also be convenient if handrails are provided all along its walls. 
	Biman Saha, Lake Town. 
